                            <comment id="12923609" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2010 20:09:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As the comment says:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+                // we used to try to avoid instantiating commitlog (thus creating an empty segment ready for writes)&lt;br/&gt;
+                // until after recover was finished.  this turns out to be fragile; it is less error-prone to go&lt;br/&gt;
+                // ahead and allow writes before recover(), and just skip active segments when we do.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12923616" author="gdusbabek" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2010 20:29:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12923688" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 21 Oct 2010 23:14:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12923826" author="hudson" created="Fri, 22 Oct 2010 12:52:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #573 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/573/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/573/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    fix commitlog recovery deleting the newly-created segment as well as the old ones&lt;br/&gt;
